Dopple spot colours can be used flat or layered. We specialise in mixing inks to create striking new shades that go beyond a single colour. Not seeing the colour you want - we can likely mix it!

is Riso PRint?

"Ri-so like Mi-so!" 

​

Riso printing is a stencil-based print process that layers vibrant soy-based inks to create unique, textured prints with distinctive tactile imperfections.

ORDER PRINTS

ECO-CONCIOUS

Dopple Press is driven by a commitment to sustainability, using 100% only premium recycled paper stock.

ORDER PRINTS

Avoid dense areas of Ink

coverage

Too much wet ink is the nemesis of riso printing.  If you don't have some areas of white or lighter coverage in your artwork this will result in roller marks, needle drag, & ink rub off.

SMOOTH or HALFTONE

dot FINISH

You can choose how you'd like 

     each colour layer printed. Either as 'Smooth' (emulating your design as closely as possible). Or as a halftone dot, unique to the machine.
